headline.print_headline: Obese Americans Spend Far More on Health Care
headline.main: Obese Americans Spend Far More on Health Care

docs.lead_paragraph: A study found that obese Americans annually spend about 42 percent more on health care than normal-weight Americans.
docs.snippet: A study found that obese Americans annually spend about 42 percent more on health care than normal-weight Americans.

headline.seo: Junior League Campaign  Emphasizes Modern Concerns

headline.seo: Manhattan’s Overweight Rate Is the Lowest in the State
